After a two-year hiatus due the Covid-19 pandemic, the colourful Cape Town Carnival is back. eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Yet another Mother City favourite has had to adjust its offering in line with COVID-19 protocols. The Cape Town Carnival is usually one big affair but this year the event will be spread across the city's streets. WATCH: Cape Town tourism industry positive over festive season numbers It'll get people moving through the city and thereby also providing much-needed support to other shops, restaurants and bars. * eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports.